name_as_recorded: "1756 Ex libris Presbiteri Joseph Marie Sormani" (inscription on flyleaf ); H. C. (Harley) Drayton (1901-1966), bought at Sotheby’s, 29 January 1951, lot 13; his sale, Sotheby’s, 12 December 1967, lot 63; re-sold at Christie’s, 28 June 1972, lot 8; Ruth E. Adomeit (1910-1996), bequeathed by her to the Lilly Library.
"Anno Domini 1548 Mensis Julio" (f. 1r); "Sold by Thomas Baker, 1, Soho Square, London" (label on front pastedown); "Cranmere Kenrick" (f. iir)
"Iste liber est domini philippi alleap(?)", 15th century (f. 1r, lower margin); "817", 19th(?) century pencil (f. 1r, upper margin); purchased from Boesen in 1959.

"Philippi Monti," f. 1; Cardinal Domenico Passionei (1682-1761); Sidney Graves Hamilton (1855-1916); his sale, Sotheby's (25 July 1917, lot 10) to Dobell. Date of acquisition by Bancroft Library UC Berkeley unrecorded. Formerly t2MS BX885 B6.
